== Install  yaml_db

$ git clone  git://github.com/lostapathy/yaml_db.git

$cd yaml_db
yaml_db$ gem build yaml_db.gemspec 
  Successfully built RubyGem
  Name: yaml_db
  Version: 0.2.2
  File: yaml_db-0.2.2.gem

yaml_db$ gem install yaml_db-0.2.2.gem 
Successfully installed yaml_db-0.2.2
1 gem installed
-----------------

== Add to Gemfile 
In case you are using "bundler", you need to add something like this to your Gemfile:

gem 'yaml_db', :git => 'git://github.com/lostapathy/yaml_db.git'

And in case there is .gemspec file, it should be able to fetch and install the gem when running bundle install.

$ rails_app> bundle install